docs.abstract: The pandemic sparked chin-up gestures like a ‘good news’ YouTube channel. Two months later, mere gestures seem pretty empty.
docs.snippet: The pandemic sparked chin-up gestures like a ‘good news’ YouTube channel. Two months later, mere gestures seem pretty empty.
docs.lead_paragraph: For two months, John Krasinski looked on the bright side. Beginning in late March and ending in late May, the actor served as the anchor for eight episodes of a YouTube show he called “Some Good News,” or “S.G.N.” for short — about 20 minutes, each week, focused entirely on feel-good content. The show was a never-ending D-block, as if that final, uplifting section of a news broadcast had been stocked with dancing health professionals and put on an endless loop.

headline.main: The Hollow Inspiration of ‘Some Good News’

docs.abstract: Between the quarantines and the demonstrations, Crisis Text Line and other mental health professionals see a rise in teen anxiety.
docs.snippet: Between the quarantines and the demonstrations, Crisis Text Line and other mental health professionals see a rise in teen anxiety.
docs.lead_paragraph: According to Nancy Lublin, the chief executive and co-founder of Crisis Text Line, a free mental health texting service providing confidential crisis intervention, the top three topics in conversations since the pandemic began have been “anxiety,” “depression” and “relationships.”

docs.abstract: The former vice president has enlisted two veteran strategists, including Senator Cory Booker’s former campaign manager, to help design a nominating convention under extraordinarily difficult circumstances.
docs.snippet: The former vice president has enlisted two veteran strategists, including Senator Cory Booker’s former campaign manager, to help design a nominating convention under extraordinarily difficult circumstances.
docs.lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has chosen two Democratic strategists to lead his preparations for the party’s summer nominating convention, a traditionally crucial event for a presidential campaign that is now enveloped in uncertainty because of the coronavirus pandemic.

headline.main: Biden Names Two New Advisers as Convention Decision Looms
headline.print_headline: Biden Names 2 New Aides For Planning Of Convention

docs.abstract: The players said they did not want a photo of them standing during the national anthem to be used for political purposes.
docs.snippet: The players said they did not want a photo of them standing during the national anthem to be used for political purposes.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a few hours this week, softball had a shot at something it has pursued for decades: the spotlight. The USSSA Pride and Scrap Yard Fast Pitch, two independent professional softball teams that feature some of the top players in the world, began what was supposed to be a seven-game series in Melbourne, Fla., facing little competition from other live sports.

headline.main: A Softball Team’s Tweet to Trump Leads Players to Quit Mid-Series
headline.print_headline: Team’s Tweet  To President  Leads Players  To Quit Series

docs.abstract: Thousands of students should have been gathering to cheer on the year’s best shows. But this isn’t a typical year.
docs.snippet: Thousands of students should have been gathering to cheer on the year’s best shows. But this isn’t a typical year.
docs.lead_paragraph: On the evening of the first Friday this month, in a tiny town in a rural Kansas county where you could have tallied the coronavirus cases on two hands and had fingers left over, Leslie Coats headed to the high school where she has taught drama for more than 40 years.

headline.main: Theater Kids Trade a Big Stage for Highlight Tapes and Heartache
headline.print_headline: High School’s Biggest Stage, Now Virtual

docs.abstract: The continuing deaths of black people by the police are undermining support for the wide latitude officers are given in cases in which an encounter ends in a death.
docs.snippet: The continuing deaths of black people by the police are undermining support for the wide latitude officers are given in cases in which an encounter ends in a death.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — The swift decision on Sunday to fire the white Atlanta police officer who shot and killed a black motorist intensified the growing re-examination of the use of deadly force by the police, challenging longstanding principles that have given law enforcement officers wide latitude in cases in which an encounter ends with a death.

headline.main: Police Killings Prompt Reassessment of Laws Allowing Deadly Force
headline.print_headline: Killing in Atlanta Refocuses Attention on Police Use of Force

byline.original: By Rick Rojas and Richard Fausset

docs.abstract: Montgomery will center her focus on the Black Lives Matter movement amid wider protests against police brutality.
docs.snippet: Montgomery will center her focus on the Black Lives Matter movement amid wider protests against police brutality.
docs.lead_paragraph: Atlanta Dream guard Renee Montgomery plans to skip the upcoming W.N.B.A. season to focus on promoting social justice causes, becoming the league’s first player to publicly opt out of the league’s plans for a shortened season during the coronavirus pandemic.

headline.main: W.N.B.A. Guard Renee Montgomery Will Skip Season to Work on Social Causes
headline.print_headline: She’ll Skip the Season to Focus on Justice
